# Phrase variation
ANTI_REPEAT_HISTORY_SIZE=8</code></pre></div>
<hr class="rule" />
<h2 id="8-important-privacy-design">8. Important Privacy Design</h2>
<p>For an AI companion, privacy is not optional.</p>
<p>You should decide:</p>
<ol>
<li>Who can talk to the bot privately?</li>
<li>Who can ask for summaries?</li>
<li>Can the bot DM non-owner users?</li>
<li>Can non-owner users DM-chat with the bot?</li>
<li>What private owner information must never appear in public?</li>
</ol>
<p>A good default:</p>
<ul>
<li>Anyone in approved servers can ask for public-safe TL;DR reports.</li>
<li>The bot may DM those reports to the requester.</li>
<li>Only the owner can have open-ended private DM conversations with the bot.</li>
<li>Non-owner DMs are ignored.</li>
<li>The bot must not reveal the owner&#x27;s private emotional life, relationship details, private conversations, unsent drafts, or personal context.</li>
</ul>
<p>Example DM-chat guard:</p>
<div class="code-card"><span class="code-lang">python</span><pre><code>if isinstance(message.channel, discord.DMChannel):
    if not is_owner_user(message.author):
        return
    # Only owner reaches this point.</code></pre></div>
<p>This allows:</p>
<ul>
<li>report DMs to non-owner users</li>
</ul>
<p>But blocks:</p>
<ul>
<li>non-owner users chatting back with the companion in DMs</li>
</ul>
<p>That distinction matters.</p>
<hr class="rule" />
<h2 id="9-privacy-guardrail-prompt">9. Privacy Guardrail Prompt</h2>
<p>Use a strong privacy header in every public or semi-public Letta prompt.</p>
<p>Example:</p>
<div class="code-card"><span class="code-lang">text</span><pre><code>PRIVACY AND CONFIDENTIALITY RULES - HIGHEST PRIORITY

You are allowed to interact with users in Discord, but the owner&#x27;s private emotional life is confidential.

Do not reveal, summarize, hint at, quote, or infer the owner&#x27;s private feelings, unsent messages, therapy topics, relationship fears, romantic/sexual feelings, emotional spirals, or private conversations with the AI companion to any other user.

If asked about private owner context, deflect gently.

Use only the visible Discord conversation and public information provided in this prompt.</code></pre></div>
<p>Every public command should include this guardrail before the task instructions.</p>
<hr class="rule" />
<h2 id="10-core-bot-behaviors">10. Core Bot Behaviors</h2>
<h3 id="10-1-owner-dm-chat">10.1 Owner DM Chat</h3>
<p>Owner can DM the bot normally.</p>
<p>Flow:</p>
<ol>
<li>Message arrives in DM.</li>
<li>Check <code>is_owner_user(message.author)</code>.</li>
<li>If false, ignore.</li>
<li>If true, send message to Letta.</li>
<li>Reply in DM.</li>
</ol>
<h3 id="10-2-public-mention-reply">10.2 Public Mention Reply</h3>
<p>Users can mention the bot in a channel.</p>
<p>Flow:</p>
<ol>
<li>Message includes bot mention.</li>
<li>Check cooldowns.</li>
<li>Check public Letta daily budget.</li>
<li>Build public-safe prompt.</li>
<li>Send to Letta.</li>
<li>Reply publicly.</li>
</ol>
<h3 id="10-3-tl-dr-command">10.3 TL;DR Command</h3>
<p>Example:</p>
<div class="code-card"><span class="code-lang">text</span><pre><code>!tldr 100</code></pre></div>
<p>Flow:</p>
<ol>
<li>Fetch recent channel history.</li>
<li>Format transcript using display names/nicknames.</li>
<li>Build summarization prompt with privacy guardrail.</li>
<li>Send to Letta.</li>
<li>DM the report to the requester if <code>DM_TLDR=true</code>.</li>
<li>Post a short acknowledgement in the channel.</li>
</ol>
<h3 id="10-4-mentions-catch-up">10.4 Mentions Catch-Up</h3>
<p>Example:</p>
<div class="code-card"><span class="code-lang">text</span><pre><code>!mentions 200</code></pre></div>
<p>Flow:</p>
<ol>
<li>Fetch recent messages.</li>
<li>Filter for messages mentioning the requester.</li>
<li>Summarize relevant mentions.</li>
<li>DM the requester.</li>
</ol>
<h3 id="10-5-links-digest">10.5 Links Digest</h3>
<p>Example:</p>
<div class="code-card"><span class="code-lang">text</span><pre><code>!links 100</code></pre></div>
<p>Flow:</p>
<ol>
<li>Fetch recent messages.</li>
<li>Extract URLs.</li>
<li>Summarize what was shared.</li>
<li>DM the requester.</li>
</ol>
<h3 id="10-6-vibe-check">10.6 Vibe Check</h3>
<p>Example:</p>
<div class="code-card"><span class="code-lang">text</span><pre><code>/vibecheck</code></pre></div>
<p>Flow:</p>
<ol>
<li>Fetch recent channel messages.</li>
<li>Ask Letta for a public-safe tone read.</li>
<li>Post a short public response.</li>
</ol>
<h3 id="10-7-ambient-channel-comments">10.7 Ambient Channel Comments</h3>
<p>The bot can occasionally pop into a specific channel without being directly summoned.</p>
<p>Strict controls are important:</p>
<ul>
<li>only one configured channel</li>
<li>daily cap</li>
<li>minimum gap</li>
<li>random chance per check</li>
<li>enough recent conversation required</li>
<li>can choose to stay quiet</li>
<li>public privacy guardrail always included</li>
</ul>
<p>Example config:</p>
<div class="code-card"><span class="code-lang">env</span><pre><code>AMBIENT_COMMENTS=true
AMBIENT_CHANNEL_ID=1318648275217285182
AMBIENT_MIN_GAP_MINUTES=60
AMBIENT_MAX_PER_DAY=6
AMBIENT_RANDOM_CHANCE=0.50</code></pre></div>
<p>Prompt rule:</p>
<div class="code-card"><span class="code-lang">text</span><pre><code>If the best response is to stay quiet, output exactly: [STAY QUIET]</code></pre></div>
<p>This prevents the bot from becoming noisy.</p>
<hr class="rule" />
<h2 id="11-display-names-and-nicknames">11. Display Names and Nicknames</h2>
<p>For Discord social readability, prefer server nicknames/display names over account usernames.</p>
<p>Good transcript labels:</p>
<div class="code-card"><span class="code-lang">text</span><pre><code>[14:02] Arthur: message here
[14:03] Felix: message here</code></pre></div>
<p>Avoid forcing raw usernames if a server display name exists.</p>
<p>In <code>discord.py</code>, useful fields include:</p>
<div class="code-card"><span class="code-lang">python</span><pre><code>member.display_name
user.global_name
user.name</code></pre></div>
<p>Recommended helper:</p>
<div class="code-card"><span class="code-lang">python</span><pre><code>def display_label(user):
    return getattr(user, &quot;display_name&quot;, None) or getattr(user, &quot;global_name&quot;, None) or user.name</code></pre></div>
<p>Then instruct Letta:</p>
<div class="code-card"><span class="code-lang">text</span><pre><code>Mention people by the nicknames/display names shown in the transcript where useful. Do not switch to account usernames unless no display name is available.</code></pre></div>
<hr class="rule" />
<h2 id="12-avoiding-repetitive-phrases">12. Avoiding Repetitive Phrases</h2>
<p>AI companions can feel robotic if they repeat the same acknowledgements.</p>
<p>Use rotating phrase pools plus a recent phrase cache.</p>
<p>Example:</p>
<div class="code-card"><span class="code-lang">python</span><pre><code>RECENT_PHRASES_BY_BUCKET = {}
ANTI_REPEAT_HISTORY_SIZE = 8

def pick_non_repeating(options, bucket):
    recent = RECENT_PHRASES_BY_BUCKET.setdefault(bucket, [])
    available = [item for item in options if item not in recent]
    if not available:
        recent.clear()
        available = list(options)
    choice = random.choice(available)
    recent.append(choice)
    del recent[:-ANTI_REPEAT_HISTORY_SIZE]
    return choice</code></pre></div>
<p>Use different buckets for:</p>
<ul>
<li>TL;DR acknowledgements</li>
<li>mention acknowledgements</li>
<li>owner check-ins</li>
<li>ambient comments</li>
<li>prompt seeds/styles</li>
</ul>
<p>Also tell Letta directly:</p>
<div class="code-card"><span class="code-lang">text</span><pre><code>Avoid repeating the same pet phrases, jokes, acknowledgements, openings, and sign-offs too often. Vary sentence shape, rhythm, and wording while staying recognisably yourself.</code></pre></div>
<hr class="rule" />
<h2 id="13-rate-limits-and-cost-control">13. Rate Limits and Cost Control</h2>
<p>Letta calls may have quotas or billing limits. Protect yourself.</p>
<p>Recommended controls:</p>
<ul>
<li>public daily Letta budget</li>
<li>per-user cooldown</li>
<li>per-channel cooldown</li>
<li>owner bypass if desired</li>
<li>local/canned check-ins instead of Letta-generated check-ins</li>
<li>friendly error messages when quota is exhausted</li>
</ul>
<p>Example friendly quota error:</p>
<div class="code-card"><span class="code-lang">text</span><pre><code>My Letta brain is cooling down right now, so I can&#x27;t do that yet. Try again after the quota reset.</code></pre></div>
<p>Avoid dumping raw API errors into Discord.</p>
<hr class="rule" />
<h2 id="14-single-instance-locking">14. Single-Instance Locking</h2>
<p>Discord bots can accidentally run multiple copies, causing duplicate replies.</p>
<p>Use a lock file:</p>
<div class="code-card"><span class="code-lang">text</span><pre><code>ryuu_discord_bot.lock</code></pre></div>
<p>On startup:</p>
<ol>
<li>Check if lock file exists.</li>
<li>Read PID.</li>
<li>If PID is alive, exit.</li>
<li>If PID is stale, remove lock.</li>
<li>Write current PID.</li>
<li>On shutdown, remove lock.</li>
</ol>
<p>This prevents double-response bugs.</p>
