<h2 id="16-common-problems-and-fixes">16. Common Problems and Fixes</h2>
<h3 id="16-1-bot-appears-offline">16.1 Bot Appears Offline</h3>
<p>Check:</p>
<ul>
<li>Is <code>python bot.py</code> running?</li>
<li>Is the lock file stale?</li>
<li>Did the bot token change?</li>
<li>Did Discord gateway disconnect?</li>
<li>Did the machine sleep?</li>
</ul>
<p>Fix:</p>
<div class="code-card"><span class="code-lang">powershell</span><pre><code>Remove-Item .\ryuu_discord_bot.lock -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
python .\bot.py</code></pre></div>
<h3 id="16-2-duplicate-replies">16.2 Duplicate Replies</h3>
<p>Likely cause: multiple bot processes are running.</p>
<p>Fix:</p>
<ul>
<li>kill all <code>python bot.py</code> processes</li>
<li>clear lock file</li>
<li>start one copy</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="16-3-raw-letta-errors-in-discord">16.3 Raw Letta Errors in Discord</h3>
<p>Do not expose raw API errors. Catch exceptions and return friendly messages.</p>
<h3 id="16-4-letta-quota-exhausted">16.4 Letta Quota Exhausted</h3>
<p>Symptoms:</p>
<ul>
<li>HTTP 402</li>
<li>rate limited</li>
<li>not enough credits</li>
<li>tier usage exceeded</li>
</ul>
<p>Fix:</p>
<ul>
<li>wait for quota reset</li>
<li>purchase credits if needed</li>
<li>reduce autonomous Letta usage</li>
<li>use local/canned check-ins</li>
<li>lower public budgets</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="16-5-non-owner-users-dm-the-bot">16.5 Non-Owner Users DM the Bot</h3>
<p>If you do not want non-owner DM chat, add:</p>
<div class="code-card"><span class="code-lang">python</span><pre><code>if isinstance(message.channel, discord.DMChannel):
    if not is_owner_user(message.author):
        return</code></pre></div>
<p>This still allows the bot to send one-way report DMs if your command handlers explicitly DM command requesters.</p>
